'''Frances Joanna Bunbury''' (b. 1814, d. 1894) was a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[botanist]], [[editor]], and [[translator]]. She was married to [[Sir Charles Bunbury, 8th Baronet]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Frances Joanna Bunbury |url=https://www.geni.com/people/Frances-Bunbury/6000000001939144412 |website=Geni.com |accessdate=3 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |title=Donations to the Library, 1894-95 |journal=Proceedings of the Linnean Society of London |date=1 November 1894 |page=59 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sggXAAAAYAAJ&pg=RA5-PA59 |accessdate=3 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Darwin |first1=Charles |editor1-last=Darwin |editor1-first=Francis |editor2-last=Seward |editor2-first=A. C. |title=More letters of Charles Darwin : a record of his work in a series of hitherto unpublished letters, Volume II |date=1903 |publisher=Appleton |location=New York |page=225 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3PcRAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA225 |accessdate=3 August 2018}}</ref>
