===Lauren Murray=== '''Lauren Murray''' (born 7 October 1990){{Citation needed|date=December 2015}} is a dental receptionist from [[North London]].{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} She was eight years old when she started singing. However, her father died when she was eleven, she lost confidence, and did not sing again until she was sixteen.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} Lauren planned to release her debut single in February 2014 available on her YouTube channel.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}}
Murray was in the bottom two in week five alongside 4th Impact and was saved by the public vote due to the judges taking the decision to deadlock. However, in week six, Murray was in the bottom two alongside Ché Chesterman where deadlock occurred once again, and public voting automatically eliminated Murray, leaving her in fourth place. Murray took part in The X Factor Live Tour 2016.
In 2015, she released the single "Each time I see you" with Marvel Riot. In 2018, she released the song "Boss girl" and the EP "Worth it".
