===Kiera Weathers=== '''Kiera Laikan Weathers''' (born 25 March 1997)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://search.findmypast.co.uk/record?id=bmd%2fb%2f1997%2f4%2f124971805|title=England & Wales births 1837-2006 Transcription for Kiera Laikan Weathers, Knowsley, 1997|accessdate=8 December 2015|via=[[Find My Past]]|subscription=yes}}</ref> is a barmaid from [[St Helens, Merseyside|St Helens]].{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}}
Weathers was in the bottom three on week one, facing the sing-off with Alien Uncovered. Weathers was saved after her mentor [[Rita Ora]], [[Nick Grimshaw]] and [[Simon Cowell]] voted to send Alien Uncovered home and [[Cheryl Fernandez-Versini]] voted to send Weathers home. Results polls released post-series revealed that Weathers had received the fewest votes in week one meaning if Cowell sent the result to deadlock, Alien Uncovered would have been saved. She was in the bottom three once again on week two, but this time received the fewest votes and was automatically eliminated, coming in eleventh place.
Kiera Weathers released her debut single 'You Gotta Be' on 9 December 2016 <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/the-x-factor/293498-x-factors-kiera-weathers-launches-brilliant-first-single-gotta.html|title=X Factor's Kiera Weathers launches brilliant first single 'You Gotta Be'}}</ref> and it was re-released on 31 March 2017 <ref>{{cite web|url=https://hypefreshmag.com/music/kiera-weathers-you-gotta-be|title=KIERA WEATHERS - "YOU GOTTA BE" - World premiering an exclusive follow-up visual to her hit single, set to turn thousands of heads.}}</ref> after she signed a record deal with Warner Music UK:
"She originally released this track in late December last year, I heard it one Saturday night and immediately knew I wanted to sign it, so I tweeted Kiera to ask if we could exchange emails. Within the course of a few hours on a Saturday evening, between Kiera and her manager, we had agreed on a deal." - Kieron Donoghue, Warner Music <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.m-magazine.co.uk/features/power-playlists-streaming-success-2017|title=PLAYLIST POWER: STREAMING SUCCESS IN 2017}}</ref> In 2017, she released the singles "Hurt so good" (feat. Marc) and "Talk to me".
