==Overs== The 'Overs' category is mentored by Simon Cowell. Contestants in the category are male and female soloists age 26+.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}}. The six candidates at judges' houses were: Bupsi, Ebru, Jennifer Phillips, Kerrie-Anne Phillips, Anton Stephans, and Max Stone.{{citation needed|date=October 2015}} Cowell chose:
===Bupsi=== '''Nicola Brown''',<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2015/09/04/x-factor-2015-bupsi-audition-lap-dance-simon-cowell-alien_n_8089822.html|title='X Factor' 2015 Contestant Bupsi Gives Simon Cowell A Lapdance During Audition, While Girlband Alien Give Us Reason To Be Excited|last=Percival|first=Ashley|date=5 September 2015|work=[[The Huffington Post UK]]|accessdate=28 October 2015}}</ref> known by her stage name '''Bupsi''', is a singer from [[Leeds]].{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} Before appearing on the show, she was working as a Tina Turner and Chic tribute act.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}}
Bupsi was automatically eliminated in week one after receiving the fewest public votes, coming in thirteenth place.
