===Max Stone=== '''Max Stone''' is a singer and songwriter from London.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} He was born in Devon and moved to Sweden when he was young. He spent twelve years there before moving back to the UK.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} Stone was influenced by his father's records and listened to soul and Motown.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} He credits music for helping him get out of his "wild child" ways.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} He wrote his first song when he was ten years old and his biggest musical achievement was performing at the Roundhouse in Camden with [[Jimmy Cliff]] and [[Maxi Priest]].{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} Max left the show in week three after being in the bottom three and being automatically eliminated as the act with the fewest public votes. He finished in ninth place.
