==Groups== The 'Groups' category is mentored by Cheryl Fernandez-Versini. Contestants in this category are either duos or vocal harmony groups, all aged sixteen and over. The six candidates at judges' houses were: 4th Impact, Alien Uncovered, BEKLN Mile, Melody Stone, New King Order, and Reggie n Bollie. Fernandez-Versini chose:
===4th Impact=== {{main|4th Impact}} '''4th Impact''' (formerly known as '''The Cercado Sisters''', '''The Cercados''', '''The''' '''Gollayan Sisters''', '''MICA,''' and '''4th Power''') are a girl group from the Philippines consisting of Almira, Irene, Mylene, and Celina Cercado<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.gmanetwork.com/news/publicaffairs/kapusomojessicasoho/546951/in-photos-4th-impact-s-journey-to-stardom/story/|title=IN PHOTOS: 4th Impact’s journey to stardom|work=GMA News Online|access-date=2017-08-25|language=en-US}}</ref> who have been singing and dancing together since 2001.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.rappler.com/entertainment/news/115882-4th-impact-x-factor-uk-concert-tour-history|title=4th Impact: More about the PH girl group, their plans after 'X Factor UK'|work=Rappler|access-date=2017-08-25|language=en}}</ref> Before ''The X Factor'', they had previously competed in several Philippine and international talent competitions.<ref name=":0" /> They are originally from [[Santiago (Philippine city)|Santiago City]] in the Philippines, but now live in [[Metro Manila]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://entertainment.inquirer.net/178467/ph-group-in-x-factor-uk-poverty-is-no-hindrance|title=PH group in ‘X Factor UK’: Poverty is no hindrance|last=Pulumbarit|first=Oliver M.|access-date=2017-08-25|language=en}}</ref>
For the first four weeks of the X Factor live shows, 4th Impact sailed through the competition, earning nothing but positive comments from the four judges for their performances.<ref name=":4">{{Cite news|url=https://spinditty.com/artists-bands/4th-Impact-Reminiscing-Their-X-Factor-UK-Journey|title=4th Impact: Reminiscing Their X-Factor UK Journey|work=Spinditty|access-date=2017-07-16|language=en}}</ref> In the fifth week of the live shows, however, the group found themselves in the bottom two for the first time in the competition. Being one of the two acts who received the fewest public votes, they had to perform against fellow contestant [[Lauren Murray]] for a place in the competition. The judges' decision on the face-off, however, were split, so the public vote was consulted and 4th Impact was eliminated, finishing in fifth place, having received the fewest votes that week.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/tv/tv-news/4th-impact-eliminated-x-factor-6924557|title=4th Impact eliminated from X Factor|last=Walker|first=Danny|date=2015-11-29|work=mirror|access-date=2017-08-25}}</ref>
After their elimination from the X Factor, 4th Impact traveled on ''[[The X Factor Live Tour]]''.<ref name=":9">{{Cite web|url=http://www.gigsandtours.com/news/acts-confirmed-for-the-x-fa-/2228|title=Gigs And Tours News|website=Gigs and Tours|language=en|access-date=2017-07-23}}</ref> Polls conducted by the show's producers prior to the tour showed 4th Impact as the most anticipated act in the tour's lineup.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.movienewsguide.com/x-factor-uk-how-4th-impact-became-in-demand/152303|title=‘X Factor’ UK: How 4th Impact Became In Demand To Fans In Upcoming Concert Tour|date=2016-02-03|work=Movie News Guide|access-date=2017-07-23|language=en-US}}</ref> Subsequently, a poll conducted after the tour named 4th Impact as the best act of the show.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/the-x-factor/254097-4th-impact-named-best-act-x-factor-2016-live-tour.html|title=4th Impact named best act of The X Factor 2016 live tour|date=2016-03-14|work=TellyMix|access-date=2017-07-23|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.movienewsguide.com/4th-impact-best-act-x-factor-2016-live-tour/178854|title=4th Impact: Best Act Of X-Factor 2016 Live Tour|date=2016-03-17|work=Movie News Guide|access-date=2017-07-23|language=en-US}}</ref> In January 2017, the group released their debut single "[[Unleash the Diva]]"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://celebmix.com/4th-impact-debut-single-unleash-the-diva/|title=4th Impact Releases Debut Single "Unleash The Diva"|date=2017-01-31|work=CelebMix|access-date=2017-08-25|language=en-GB|author=Currinn, Jonathan}}</ref>
