===Alien Uncovered=== '''Alien Uncovered''' (formerly '''Alien''') are a five-piece girl group consisting of Madison, Natalie, Shae, Temple,{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} and Yasmin "Yaz" Crotch.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thecomet.net/news/after_wowing_judges_on_the_x_factor_two_stevenage_performers_cruise_through_to_boot_camp_1_4227752|title=After wowing judges on the X Factor two Stevenage performers cruise through to boot camp|last=Pritchard|first=Oliver|date=10 September 2015|work=The Comet|publisher=Archant Community Media|accessdate=9 December 2015}}</ref> During their time on the show, they also had a sixth member, Frank. The band came up with their name after people kept staring at them on a train because of the way they looked, stating: "We felt like aliens... so we thought it would be a good name for the band."{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} They have been together for over a year and are all former dancers.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}}
Alien Uncovered were eliminated in week one after ending up in the sing-off with Kiera Weathers, receiving [[Rita Ora]]'s, [[Nick Grimshaw]]'s and [[Simon Cowell]]'s votes to be sent home but [[Cheryl Fernandez-Versini]] (their mentor) voted to save them. Result polls released after the end of the series revealed that if Cowell sent the vote to deadlock, Alien Uncovered would've been saved. They finished in 12th place. A few days before their group performance with the other contestants at the final, Frank abruptly left the band, later claiming she was being forced to by the other members.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tellymix.co.uk/reality-tv/the-x-factor/243430-x-factors-alien-uncovered-lose-a-member-ahead-of-the-final.html|title=X Factor's Alien Uncovered lose a member and it turns BITCHY &#124; The X Factor 2017 &#124; TellyMix|last=Darvill|first=Josh|date=12 December 2015|accessdate=25 July 2017}}</ref> In 2017, the girl group released their debut single "[[Handle It]]".
