===Reggie 'n' Bollie=== {{main|Reggie 'n' Bollie}} '''Reggie 'n' Bollie''' (formerly '''Menn on Poinnt''') are a duo from [[Ghana]] consisting of Reggie Zippy<ref name="Reggie Zippy">{{cite web|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/entertainment/See-what-Reggie-Zippy-has-been-doing-in-UK-since-he-left-Ghana-384320|title=See what Reggie Zippy has been doing in UK since he left Ghana|date=27 September 2015|publisher=GhanaWeb|accessdate=20 November 2015}}</ref> (born Reginald Anusson, 15 July 1984){{Citation needed|date=February 2016}} and Bollie Babeface{{Citation needed|date=February 2016}} (born Ishmael Hamid,<ref name="Bollie">{{cite web|url=http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/people/person.php?ID=276|title=Bollie|publisher=GhanaWeb|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref> 2 July 1986).{{Citation needed|date=February 2016}} They have been living in the UK with their families for the past five years.{{Citation needed|date=November 2015}} The pair both separately released [[Hiplife]] style music in Ghana.<ref name="sun">{{cite web|url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/showbiz/6801867/X-Factor-finalists-Reggie-N-Bollie-have-already-had-big-hits-in-Africa.html|title=X Factor finalists Reggie 'N' Bollie already had big hits in Africa|publisher=}}</ref> Reggie released three songs in 2006 called "Virgin", "4 Sale" and "Adoma".<ref name="Reggie Zippy" /> In 2004, Bollie also had a hit, "You May Kiss the Bride"<ref name="Bollie" /> popular at weddings.<ref name="sun"/> With the eliminations of Alien Uncovered in week one and 4th Impact in week five, Reggie 'n' Bollie became Fernandez-Versini's sole remaining act in the competition and subsequently were announced as runners-up in the final, losing out to Louisa Johnson. They took part in The X Factor Live Tour 2016.
Reggie 'n' Bollie signed to [[Syco Music]] on 20 January 2016. They released their first single "[[New Girl (Reggie 'N' Bollie song)|New Girl]]" on 13 May through Syco.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/reggie-n-bollie-sign-to-simon-cowells-syco-label__13592/|title=Reggie N Bollie sign to Simon Cowell's Syco label|last=Copsey|first=Rob|date=20 January 2016|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=20 January 2016}}</ref>
