'''Raquel Pa'aluhi''' (born October 14, 1990) is an [[United States|American]] [[mixed martial arts|mixed martial artist]] who competes in the [[Bantamweight (MMA)|Bantamweight]] division. She is a wrestler/striker who started her career in Hawai'i and has since made Las Vegas her home. After her title fight loss to Yana Kunitskaya on the 31st of August 2017 she was awarded her Black Belt in Brazilian jiu-jitsu by her coach [[Robert Drysdale]]. Raquel is the 2014, 2015 & 2016 No Gi World Champion and 2017 World Jiu-Jitsu Championship Gi Brown Belt Runner Up.<ref>{{cite news|title= Raquel Paaluhi representing the warrior spirit of Hawaii|publisher= [[Bleacher Report]]|date=|url= http://bleacherreport.com/articles/2426990-invicta-12s-raquel-paaluhi-representing-the-warrior-spirit-of-hawaii|accessdate=2015-04-16}}</ref> She is currently signed to [[Invicta Fighting Championships|Invicta FC]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Video: Invicta FC 9 results: Honchak grinds out win, Kowalkiewicz upsets Inoue|publisher= [[MMAJunkie]]|date=|url= http://mmajunkie.com/2014/11/invicta-fc-9-live-results-and-fight-recaps|accessdate=2015-04-13}}</ref>
==Personal life== Pa'aluhi is of [[Native Hawaiians|Hawaiian]], [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]], [[Samoans|Samoan]], [[Germans|German]], and [[Irish people|Irish]] descent.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Paaluhi |first1=Raquel |title=my ethnicities are mostly Hawaiian and Portugese but a little German Irish and Samoan too |url=https://twitter.com/RaquelPaaluhi/status/84845885959315456 |publisher=Twitter |accessdate=25 June 2011}}</ref> In 2016, she married Brazilian Renato Canuto who is a black belt and also a World Champion in Jiu-jitsu.<ref>{{cite web |title=Raquel Pa'aluhi Canuto |url=https://kekoacollective.com/pages/raquel-canuto |publisher=Kekoa Collective |accessdate=10 June 2018}}</ref>
